HEADWORD: Pullet
<hw>Pul"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>polete</ets>, OF. <ets>polete</ets>, F. <ets>poulette</ets>, dim.
of <ets>poule</ets> a hen, fr. L. <ets>pullus</ets> a young animal, a
young fowl. See <er>Foal</er>, and cf. <er>Poult</er>, <er>Poultry</er>,
<er>Pool</er> stake.]</ety> <def>A young hen, or female of the domestic
fowl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pullet sperm</b></col>, <cd>the treadle of an egg.</cd>
